《'''權力的48條法則'''》（{{lang-en|''The 48 Laws of Power''}}）為美國作家[[羅伯特·格林_(作家)|羅伯特·格林]]於1998年出版的一本[[非虛構作品|非虛構]]著作。<ref name=48lawsofpower>{{cite book |title=The 48 Laws of Power |last=Greene |first=Robert|year=2000 |location=New York, NY |isbn=0140280197 |pages=452 }}</ref>本書為[[暢銷書|暢銷書]]<ref name=NYTimesBestSellers>{{cite web|title=Business Bestsellers|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1998/11/08/business/the-new-york-times-business-best-sellers.html|work=New York Times|date=1998-11-08|access-date=2020-09-13|archive-date=2019-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704122738/https://www.nytimes.com/1998/11/08/business/the-new-york-times-business-best-sellers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=BusinessWeek>{{cite news|last=Green|first=Hardy|title=Best Selling List|work=[[Bloomberg_Businessweek|BusinessWeek]]}}</ref>，於全美國賣出超過120萬本<ref name=LATimes-in-house-guru/>，尤其受到不少名人和服刑中的囚犯喜愛。<ref name=LATimes-in-house-guru>Chang, Andrea. [http://articles.latimes.com/2011/aug/30/business/la-fi-robert-greene-20110726 American Apparel's in-house guru shows a lighter side] {{Wayback|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2011/aug/30/business/la-fi-robert-greene-20110726 |date=20180507062830 }}. ''LA Times''. 2011-08-30.</ref><ref name=CNN>Blake, John. [http://www.cnn.com/2010/LIVING/worklife/03/15/48.laws.of.power/ How to Master the ‘48 Laws of Power’] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/LIVING/worklife/03/15/48.laws.of.power/ |date=20191230121319 }}. ''CNN''. 2010-03-15.</ref><ref name=OutlawCulture/><ref name=Entrepreneur>Tice, Carol. [http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/168770 All’s Fair?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/168770 |date=20190608151139 }}. ''Entrepreneur''. 2006-11-01.</ref><ref name=NewYorker>Paumgarten, Nick. [http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2006/11/06/061106fa_fact_paumgarten Fresh Prince] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2006/11/06/061106fa_fact_paumgarten |date=20140630154002 }}. ''New Yorker''. 2006-11-06.</ref>

== 背景 ==
格林回憶，讓自己決定要撰寫本書的動機源自自己在[[好萊塢|好萊塢]]擔任編劇時的經驗，他注意到當今社會的統治菁英在許多特質上和歷史上一些權傾一時的人物並無不同。<ref name="CNN"/>1995年，當時在義大利法布立卡藝術暨媒體學校擔任駐校作家的格林遇到了書籍包裝商約斯特·埃爾弗斯。<ref name="LATimes-in-house-guru"/><ref name="NewYorker"/>六個月後，格林將自己
想要寫書的想法和書中可能出現的內容概略地和埃爾弗斯討論，埃爾弗斯並建議格林開始擬稿。<ref name=LATimes-in-house-guru/>

儘管當時格林並不喜歡自己的工作，但對於寫書的想法相當猶豫，認為既費時也存在不少風險。<ref name=Forbes>Perlroth, Nicole. [https://www.forbes.com/2009/06/18/robert-greene-classics-leadership-greene.html Robert Greene on Power Ambition Glory] {{Wayback|url=https://www.forbes.com/2009/06/18/robert-greene-classics-leadership-greene.html |date=20170519154519 }}. ''Forbes''. 2009-06-16.</ref> 不過，當時格林也在重新溫讀自己最喜歡的一本有關[[尤利烏斯·凱撒|尤利烏斯·凱撒]]的人物誌，書中凱撒決定跨越[[盧比孔河|盧比孔河]]向[[格奈烏斯·龐培|格奈烏斯·龐培]]宣戰並發動[[凱撒內戰|凱撒內戰]]的事蹟使作者得到啟發<ref name=Forbes/>，毅然決定完成初稿。初稿便是日後《權力的48條法則》的雛形<ref name=Forbes/>，由於該書大賣，作者因此稱寫書的決定是自己人生中的一大轉捩點。<ref name=Forbes/>

